@startuml
' @id(DOM-FONT-DATABASE)
' Objective-only domain concept: the font database the SVG rasterizer
' depends on. Absent on the current side (the code uses an empty default)
' — this is the parity gap that /mdd-review surfaces and /mdd-implement closes.
title Font database for SVG rasterization (objective)

class SvgRasterizer {
  + parse(bytes) : Tree
  + render(tree, scale) : Pixmap
}

class FontDatabase {
  + fontCount : int
  + defaultFamily : String
  + loadSystemFonts() : void
}

SvgRasterizer "1" o-- "1" FontDatabase : resolves <text> via >

note bottom of FontDatabase
  Populated once with the host's system fonts
  before the first parse/render. Constrained by
  OCL-FONTDB-POPULATED. When the code is fixed,
  /mdd-map derives this class on the current side
  and ID parity closes.
end note
@enduml
